Vice President Kamala Harris and European Commission President Ursula von der Leyen had a discussion on coordinated actions between the US and the EU in response to Russia's invasion of Ukraine. They talked about imposing severe economic consequences on Russia and its accomplices, as well as ensuring that Russia continues to face high costs for its aggression. The leaders also discussed the increasing number of people fleeing violence in Ukraine, with the Vice President emphasizing the US commitment to providing humanitarian assistance to those in need. They agreed to work together in providing life-saving aid to the vulnerable, and the Vice President expressed appreciation for the generosity and kindness shown by EU leaders and the European people.